          <p id="PIF-SEC.IO.92">The first annual meeting of South Pacific heads of state and of government was held in August 1971, in Wellington, New Zealand. A secretariat was established (as the South Pacific Bureau for Economic Co-operation—SPEC) by an agreement signed in April 1973. SPEC was redesignated as the South Pacific Forum Secretariat in 1988, and the present name was adopted in October 2000, in order to reflect the expansion of its membership since its establishment. In October 2005 the 36th Forum adopted an Agreement Establishing the Pacific Islands Forum, which form­alized the grouping's status as a full intergovernmental organization.</p>
